CONDITIONS

1. COPYLEFT
Any modified version or derivative work must be distributed under this same
license, with full source code made publicly available.

2. ATTRIBUTION
All copies and derivatives must retain this license and the following notice:
"Traffic camera data provided by Georgia 511 (511ga.org), operated by the
Georgia Department of Transportation. Use of this data is subject to 511GA's
terms of service."

3. NO DATA HOARDING
This software and any derivative may not store, log, archive, or redistribute
511GA camera feeds, snapshots, or metadata beyond what is necessary for
real-time display. Camera data must be fetched live and never persisted to a
database or third-party server.

4. ZERO LOGS PROMISE
This software does not and must not log, track, or transmit user activity, API
keys, search queries, or any personally identifiable information. Any derivative
must uphold this guarantee and clearly state it in their documentation.

5. NON-COMMERCIAL DATA USE
The 511GA data accessed through this software may not be used for commercial
purposes. This restriction applies to all derivatives.

6. API KEY RESPONSIBILITY
This software does not include an API key. If you distribute a copy or
derivative of this software, you must not embed or share your own 511GA API key
in the distributed code. Each person who receives your distribution is
responsible for obtaining their own free API key from 511ga.org/developers/doc
and complying with 511GA's terms of service independently.

7. ZERO RESPONSIBILITY
No individual, group, community, or entity — including anyone who has
contributed to, distributed, or used this software — bears any responsibility
for its use, misuse, or consequences. The name PeachFlow is unclaimed and
unowned. Responsibility for misuse lies with nobody. No party can be held liable
for any damages, direct or indirect, arising from the use of this software.
Misuse is solely the burden of the person committing it.

